org.bytedeco.arrow

Class SubTreeFileSystem

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bytedeco.javacpp.Pointer
      • org.bytedeco.arrow.FileSystem
        • org.bytedeco.arrow.SubTreeFileSystem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    @Namespace(value="arrow::fs")
 @NoOffset
 @Properties(inherit=arrow.class)
public class SubTreeFileSystem
extends FileSystem
    \brief A FileSystem implementation that delegates to another implementation after prepending a fixed base path. This is useful to expose a logical view of a subtree of a filesystem, for example a directory in a LocalFileSystem. This works on abstract paths, i.e. paths using forward slashes and and a single root "/". Windows paths are not guaranteed to work. This makes no security guarantee. For example, symlinks may allow to "escape" the subtree and access other parts of the underlying filesystem.
